  KEY OBSERVATIONS:
  Phi_1(2) = 1: trivial
  Phi_2(2) = 3: our FUNDAMENTAL 3!
  Phi_3(2) = 7: tournament n=7!
  Phi_6(2) = 3: also 3 (since Phi_6(x) = x^2-x+1, 4-2+1=3)
  2^n - 1 = prod_(d|n) Phi_d(2)
  So 2^6-1 = 63 = 1*3*7*3 = Phi_1*Phi_2*Phi_3*Phi_6
  And 63 = 9*7 = 3^2 * 7

  H = 63 (= 2^6 - 1): is it achievable at n=7?
  NOT FOUND in 200 samples

